      <div class="span-24 headline">
        <h1>Zope Component Architecture on Google App Engine</h1>
        <hr>
        <h2 class="emph">
          Bring together what belongs together - growing with modern building
          materials.
        </h2>
      </div>
      <hr>
      <div class="span-17 colborder">
        <p>
          The <strong>Zope Component Architecture (ZCA)</strong> is a Python
          framework for supporting component based design and programming. The
          ZCA is not specific to the <a href="http://www.zope.org">Zope</a>
          web application server. Therefore using the ZCA within
          <a href="http://code.google.com/appengine">Google App Engine</a> is
          very interesting in many ways.
        </p>
        <img class="right" src="/images/stack.jpg" />
        <p>
          The diagram shows a relatively small stack of components running under
          the hood of this demo. It uses the ZCA for implementing views
          (adapter) and a global session management utility.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="span-6 last">
        <h3>What <span class="emph">is</span> the ZCA?</h3>
        <p>
          The ZCA is all about using Python objects effectively. Components are
          reusable objects with introspectable interfaces. An interface is an
          object that describes how you work with a particular component. It
          doesn't matter how the component is implemented, the important part
          is that it comply with its interface contracts.
        </p>
        <p>
          <a href="http://muthukadan.net/docs/zca.html">Comprehensive Guide to
          the Zope Component Architecture</a>.
        </p>
        <h3>What do <span class="emph">you</span> think?</h3>
        <span class="emph"
              tal:condition="view/status"
              tal:content="view/status" />
        <form id="comments" action="/" method="post">
          <label for="content">Leave a comment if you like.</label>
          <textarea name="content" class="span-6 comments"></textarea>
          <input type="submit" value="Submit">
        </form>
        <div tal:replace="structure view/greetings" />
      </div>
